Interface CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback

  • Enclosing interface:
    CameraCaptureSession

    public static interface CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback

    A callback object for tracking the progress of a CameraCaptureRequest submitted to the camera device.

      • onNewFrame

        void onNewFrame(CameraCaptureSession session,
                CameraCaptureRequest request,
                CameraFrame cameraFrame)
        This method is called when an image capture has fully completed and a newly captured frame is available.
        Parameters:
        session - the session returned by Camera.createCaptureSession(<any>)
        request - the request that was given to the Camera
        cameraFrame - the newly available frame
        See Also:
        CameraCaptureSession.startCapture(org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.external.hardware.camera.CameraCaptureRequest, org.firstinspires.ftc.robotcore.external.hardware.camera.CameraCaptureSession.CaptureCallback, <any>)
